data.description: BEST OF BOTH WORLDS!!!! This home is private but close to town and the lake  If  you are looking for a place to call home, where your kids can be picked up on Delph Lane and dropped off at Mooresburg School, this place is right for you. It has beautiful mountain and seasonal lake views from the front porch, where you can sit and enjoy your morning coffee while watching the wildlife in your front yard. This two story log cabin is situated on 2.57 acres. It has beautiful refinished hardwood floors throughout, tongue and groove walls in the living room and a gas fireplace. It has an open concept kitchen that has beautiful cabinets with granite counter tops, a new granite kitchen island and stainless steel appliances. The spacious laundry room has new stainless steel touch screen, Samsung washer and dryer. The dining area overlooks the newly fenced back yard. French doors lead to the sunroom, which leads to the ramp to access the home from the back to bring groceries easily into the home. The large primary bedroom is on the main level . The  full bath on the main level has a walk in shower and tile floors. 2 bedrooms and a full bath are on the second floor. The basement offers an additional 1200 square feet of unfinished space that could be converted to living space.  There is a  drive under garage and another exterior door in the basement. The exterior was recently stained and sealed.The The entire deck has just been repainted.  UNRESTRICTED!!!  FIBER OPTIC INTERNET!!! Solar gate, paved driveway and a detached carport for your boat or RV are more amenities. Clinch View Golf Course and Country Club are only a mile away. Cherokee Lake boat access is only a 0.2 mile drive and Cherokee Lake public fishing pier is 6 minutes away, Convenient location- 1 hour to Dollywood or Gatlinburg, Knoxville, Johnson City and Bristol Motor Speedway. Don't let this residential or investment property get away. Information deemed reliable but not guaranteed. Buyer/buyrs agent
